  "texts": [
    "This indicates an average increase in the attack success rate of 93.0% when Dis-tillSeq is utilized, compared to scenarios where it is absent.",
    "Our results highlight significant limitations in current safety alignments and offer a more efficient approach for testing these models.Overall, we make the following contributions:• Knowledge Distillation for LLM Safety Alignment: We propose a novel knowledge distillation method to transfer moderation knowledge from LLMs to smaller, more efficient distilled models.",
    "• Effective Testing Framework: We propose an automated testing framework called DistillSeq, designed to generate malicious queries using syntax tree-based and LLM-based approaches.",
    "These queries are subsequently filtered using distilled models to identify effective queries for testing the LLM.",
    "• Empirical Evidence of Method Effectiveness: We evaluated DistillSeq on four mainstream LLMs."
  ]
}